This article is part of the series: Politics and government of Liguria  The Ligurian regional election of 1975 took place on 15 June 1975. The Italian Communist Party was the largest party, largely ahead of Christian Democracy. After the election, Communist Angelo Carossino formed a government comprising also the Italian Socialist Party. Carossino was replaced by Armando Magliotto in 1979. Source: Ministry of the Interior 
